    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Plays streaming TTS audio from a server-side agent through a USoundWaveProcedural fed by a hidden UAudioComponent.</para>
<para>Wire it up by assigning this component to the Speaker slot on a <ref refid="class_u_tryll_agent_component" kindref="compound">UTryllAgentComponent</ref>; the agent forwards TTS audio frames here.</para>
<sect1 id="class_u_tryll_speaker_component_1autotoc_md0_1s1"><sect2 id="class_u_tryll_speaker_component_1autotoc_md0">
<title>Threading</title><para>HandleFormat and HandleAudio fire on the game thread (drained by UTryllSubsystem::Tick). USoundWaveProcedural::QueueAudio is internally thread-safe — it copies into its own consumer queue, which the audio mixer thread drains.</para>
</sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="class_u_tryll_speaker_component_1autotoc_md1_1s1"><sect2 id="class_u_tryll_speaker_component_1autotoc_md1">
<title>End-of-stream</title><para>TtsAudioFrame carries no is_final flag — the turn ends with TurnComplete. Audio drains naturally; OnTtsAudioFinished fires when the procedural sound&apos;s queue empties and the UAudioComponent stops. </para>
</sect2></sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
